1
00:00:50,154 --> 00:00:51,239
ALL FIGURES,
INCIDENTS, LOCATIONS,

2
00:00:51,322 --> 00:00:52,574
ORGANIZATIONS,
AND OTHERS ARE FICTITIOUS.

3
00:00:52,657 --> 00:00:54,075
CHILD ACTORS AND ANIMALS
WERE FILMED SAFELY

4
00:00:54,159 --> 00:00:55,076
IN ACCORDANCE WITH GUIDELINES.

5
00:01:27,734 --> 00:01:29,110
What brings you here, Mr. Attorney?

6
00:01:30,653 --> 00:01:31,988
Why are you here?

7
00:01:35,116 --> 00:01:36,618
I don't know.

8
00:01:36,701 --> 00:01:40,830
I went wherever my feet took me
and ended up here.

9
00:01:44,083 --> 00:01:45,543
Why haven't you…

10
00:01:47,462 --> 00:01:49,047
burned the talisman yet?

11
00:01:52,050 --> 00:01:53,343
I'm not sure.

12
00:01:55,136 --> 00:01:56,387
Maybe I wanted to find

13
00:01:57,722 --> 00:02:00,850
even just a tiny excuse not to burn it.

14
00:02:04,312 --> 00:02:05,313
But…

15
00:02:07,607 --> 00:02:09,651
the more I listened to others…

16
00:02:12,278 --> 00:02:13,863
the more my disappointment grew.

17
00:02:19,118 --> 00:02:20,119
Now…

18
00:02:21,287 --> 00:02:23,122
I'm done looking for excuses.

19
00:02:26,709 --> 00:02:28,169
Despite what others say,

20
00:02:29,212 --> 00:02:30,296
I've decided

21
00:02:32,048 --> 00:02:33,633
to believe…

22
00:02:36,844 --> 00:02:38,429
what I know and remember of you.

23
00:02:47,188 --> 00:02:48,856
You were born

24
00:02:50,692 --> 00:02:52,026
on August 15, 1963.

25
00:02:53,945 --> 00:02:55,113
Your name is Shin Gi-jung.

26
00:02:59,617 --> 00:03:00,618
You are…

27
00:03:05,248 --> 00:03:06,749
my father.

28
00:03:20,722 --> 00:03:22,807
-Dad!
-Sa-rang.

29
00:03:25,226 --> 00:03:27,103
All right. Let's play catch, I-rang.

30
00:03:27,895 --> 00:03:29,147
Good?

31
00:03:37,530 --> 00:03:38,656
Dad!

32
00:04:23,409 --> 00:04:24,410
You are…

33
00:04:24,494 --> 00:04:25,495
Dad!

34
00:04:37,507 --> 00:04:38,508
…my son…

35
00:04:41,344 --> 00:04:42,678
I-rang.

36
00:04:45,973 --> 00:04:47,350
Dad…

37
00:04:50,395 --> 00:04:51,437
I-rang.

38
00:05:33,646 --> 00:05:35,148
Your hands used to be so tiny.

39
00:05:37,483 --> 00:05:38,860
They're so big now.

40
00:05:46,450 --> 00:05:47,451
Your mom…

41
00:05:50,580 --> 00:05:51,581
is well, right?

42
00:05:55,376 --> 00:05:56,377
She is.

43
00:06:00,339 --> 00:06:01,340
And healthy?

44
00:06:03,217 --> 00:06:05,344
Yes, she's very healthy.

45
00:06:07,346 --> 00:06:08,347
What about Sa-rang?

46
00:06:09,098 --> 00:06:10,099
Oh, right.

47
00:06:10,892 --> 00:06:13,978
The paralegal called you
his brother-in-law.

48
00:06:16,689 --> 00:06:18,274
He must be my son-in-law.

49
00:06:20,109 --> 00:06:21,110
That's right.

50
00:06:22,153 --> 00:06:25,698
He's a little silly and off the wall,

51
00:06:26,490 --> 00:06:29,869
-he's really--
-Nice, I know. He's a good man.

52
00:06:31,662 --> 00:06:33,247
I only got to talk to him a little,

53
00:06:34,832 --> 00:06:36,125
but I could tell right away.

54
00:06:49,597 --> 00:06:52,808
This is where Mom works.

55
00:06:53,392 --> 00:06:55,728
Your mom runs a butcher's?

56
00:06:57,355 --> 00:06:58,356
Yes.

57
00:06:58,981 --> 00:07:01,901
And right next to it
is the restaurant that Sa-rang runs.

58
00:07:02,902 --> 00:07:04,820
This is totally unexpected.

59
00:07:05,404 --> 00:07:08,783
It's quite famous in this neighborhood.

60
00:07:10,034 --> 00:07:11,202
I see.

61
00:07:14,330 --> 00:07:15,790
Let's go inside.

62
00:07:16,374 --> 00:07:17,375
Wait.

63
00:07:18,751 --> 00:07:21,337
You'd better go alone for now.

64
00:07:22,630 --> 00:07:24,882
They might be shocked if you possess me.

65
00:07:25,883 --> 00:07:27,468
I'll wait at my office.

66
00:07:28,928 --> 00:07:30,012
All right.

67
00:07:47,572 --> 00:07:49,865
When you aren't sure about yourself,

68
00:07:50,491 --> 00:07:53,828
take a deep breath and think to yourself
that you can do it.

69
00:07:53,911 --> 00:07:56,414
It will bring you real courage.

70
00:08:24,692 --> 00:08:26,277
Can you do this for me?

71
00:08:47,256 --> 00:08:48,382
Honey.

72
00:09:21,290 --> 00:09:22,875
Here you go. Enjoy.

73
00:09:22,958 --> 00:09:24,669
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

74
00:09:24,752 --> 00:09:25,753
Thank you.

75
00:09:32,551 --> 00:09:34,679
-You ordered the spicy pork, right?
-Yes.

76
00:09:35,721 --> 00:09:37,348
Here you go.

77
00:09:37,431 --> 00:09:40,559
Your spicy pork. And here's the stew.
Be careful, it's hot.

78
00:09:40,643 --> 00:09:43,145
-Let me know if you need anything.
-Dad!

79
00:09:43,938 --> 00:09:46,357
I want ice cream.

80
00:09:46,440 --> 00:09:47,858
-"Dad"?
-Buy me ice cream.

81
00:09:47,942 --> 00:09:49,276
Ice cream?

82
00:09:49,902 --> 00:09:54,740
You already had chips earlier.
Save ice cream for tomorrow, Da-bong.

83
00:09:54,824 --> 00:09:58,077
-You must be my granddaughter.
-Ice cream and chips are different.

84
00:09:58,619 --> 00:10:00,413
-Yes, I know.
-Da-bong…

85
00:10:00,496 --> 00:10:04,375
-I do, but your mom doesn't.
-What a lovely name.

86
00:10:04,458 --> 00:10:06,961
Hmph. I hate you, Mom!

87
00:10:07,044 --> 00:10:08,504
I hate you too!

88
00:10:08,587 --> 00:10:10,089
Da-bong.

89
00:10:12,299 --> 00:10:15,469
Watch how you speak to your dad.

90
00:10:17,638 --> 00:10:18,681
Sa-rang?

91
00:10:22,309 --> 00:10:23,310
My daughter…

92
00:10:25,855 --> 00:10:27,148
My sweetheart, Sa-rang.

93
00:10:36,574 --> 00:10:37,950
Welcome.

94
00:10:40,619 --> 00:10:43,789
Da-bong, we'll talk again later.

95
00:10:44,415 --> 00:10:46,792
-No.
-What do you mean, no?

96
00:10:48,502 --> 00:10:50,379
Were you being good or naughty?

97
00:10:50,463 --> 00:10:52,840
-Pork belly, sir? Got it.
-I was naughty.

98
00:11:03,184 --> 00:11:04,310
I-rang.

99
00:11:06,479 --> 00:11:08,481
You must have
a lot of questions to ask me.

100
00:11:09,940 --> 00:11:10,941
What?

101
00:11:11,025 --> 00:11:13,861
You said I deceived people.

102
00:11:17,239 --> 00:11:18,240
Also…

103
00:11:19,533 --> 00:11:22,495
you said that
I'd want to die again out of shame

104
00:11:23,287 --> 00:11:24,747
if you told me who I was.

105
00:11:26,582 --> 00:11:30,503
Can you tell me why you said such a thing?

106
00:11:32,588 --> 00:11:34,548
I honestly don't remember

107
00:11:35,508 --> 00:11:37,051
my last moment.

108
00:11:38,928 --> 00:11:41,138
Nor do I remember how I died.

109
00:11:42,264 --> 00:11:43,849
What I can recall is

110
00:11:44,391 --> 00:11:47,895
that I was on my way
to collect crucial evidence

111
00:11:48,729 --> 00:11:51,440
for Mr. Yoon's case that day.

112
00:11:56,779 --> 00:11:58,197
Three minutes left to arrive.

113
00:12:22,888 --> 00:12:24,056
I'm not sure

114
00:12:25,808 --> 00:12:27,017
what happened next.

115
00:12:28,644 --> 00:12:30,229
There was an accident.

116
00:12:40,864 --> 00:12:42,616
You were taken to the ER,

117
00:12:44,326 --> 00:12:45,995
but you died

118
00:12:47,580 --> 00:12:49,123
before we arrived.

119
00:12:52,293 --> 00:12:53,294
And…

120
00:12:57,339 --> 00:12:58,382
I…

121
00:13:01,552 --> 00:13:03,971
want to hear your side of the story,

122
00:13:05,681 --> 00:13:08,934
not what others say about you.

123
00:13:23,907 --> 00:13:25,701
What I know…

124
00:13:29,246 --> 00:13:30,372
Okay.

125
00:13:40,090 --> 00:13:44,637
The first time I met Mr. Yoon was
because of a school violence case.

126
00:13:45,512 --> 00:13:48,724
Public outrage was boiling over
with a lot of people saying

127
00:13:48,807 --> 00:13:51,393
that the teacher ruined a student
through excessive punishment.

128
00:13:51,477 --> 00:13:53,354
But when we first met,

129
00:13:55,272 --> 00:13:57,983
Mr. Yoon was quite firm.

130
00:13:59,068 --> 00:14:03,989
A teacher must teach their students
to be responsible for their mistakes.

131
00:14:05,240 --> 00:14:06,408
I see.

132
00:14:06,492 --> 00:14:07,493
INVESTIGATION REPORT

133
00:14:11,038 --> 00:14:12,039
INTERROGATION REPORT

134
00:14:16,752 --> 00:14:18,045
EXPULSION WAS ENFORCED

135
00:14:19,171 --> 00:14:20,631
CRIMINAL AND INVESTIGATION RECORDS

136
00:14:21,215 --> 00:14:23,133
Upon actual investigation,

137
00:14:23,217 --> 00:14:26,387
it turned out that the teacher's decision
about the bullies was fair.

138
00:14:32,434 --> 00:14:34,728
-No!
-Damn, it stinks so much.

139
00:14:34,812 --> 00:14:38,273
For the breach of Article 17,
the duty to maintain good conduct,

140
00:14:38,357 --> 00:14:39,483
I order your expulsion.

141
00:14:39,566 --> 00:14:41,402
-What? Expulsion?
-It's not…

142
00:14:41,485 --> 00:14:42,486
I said it's not my fault.

143
00:14:42,569 --> 00:14:44,363
There was nothing legally wrong, either.

144
00:14:44,446 --> 00:14:46,365
NO GROUNDS FOR SUSPICION

145
00:14:46,991 --> 00:14:49,702
So, I decided not to prosecute him

146
00:14:49,785 --> 00:14:52,746
and thought the case was over.

147
00:14:52,830 --> 00:14:54,957
MAY 12
YOON DAE-MYEONG

148
00:14:55,958 --> 00:14:57,334
"Yoon Dae-myeong"?

149
00:14:58,168 --> 00:15:00,254
But a few days later,

150
00:15:00,337 --> 00:15:04,717
a flood of lawsuits and complaints
against Mr. Yoon began to pour in.

151
00:15:05,467 --> 00:15:10,222
Complainants were parents, colleagues,
and even outside figures.

152
00:15:10,931 --> 00:15:13,142
The cases were all different too.

153
00:15:13,225 --> 00:15:16,979
Mr. Yoon openly humiliated my daughter.

154
00:15:17,688 --> 00:15:20,733
It mentally traumatized her.

155
00:15:20,816 --> 00:15:24,028
Rumors said he touched female students.

156
00:15:24,111 --> 00:15:27,281
He called them in for counseling
and sneakily touched them.

157
00:15:27,364 --> 00:15:30,034
There's a rumor that
he takes bribes from parents

158
00:15:30,117 --> 00:15:32,953
and treats school funds for personal use.

159
00:15:33,037 --> 00:15:35,998
It shows he lacks a moral compass.

160
00:15:39,877 --> 00:15:41,587
Since the complaints were filed,

161
00:15:41,670 --> 00:15:44,506
I had no choice
but to investigate as a prosecutor.

162
00:15:44,590 --> 00:15:45,966
My conclusion was

163
00:15:46,050 --> 00:15:48,594
that Mr. Yoon was moral

164
00:15:49,553 --> 00:15:51,346
and upright.

165
00:15:51,930 --> 00:15:53,015
The problem was that

166
00:15:53,599 --> 00:15:56,769
a person like him could be…

167
00:15:58,854 --> 00:16:01,065
an eyesore for some people.

168
00:16:02,858 --> 00:16:04,318
An eyesore?

169
00:16:07,446 --> 00:16:09,490
I thought this series of complaints

170
00:16:09,573 --> 00:16:15,120
wasn't simply out of
a misunderstanding or hostility,

171
00:16:16,455 --> 00:16:19,166
but an intentional act
to bring Mr. Yoon down.

172
00:16:20,626 --> 00:16:24,588
I was aware of the sheer tenacity
of those who cunningly exploit the law,

173
00:16:26,256 --> 00:16:28,425
so I carefully gave him a piece of advice.

174
00:16:29,259 --> 00:16:30,260
Mr. Yoon.

175
00:16:31,553 --> 00:16:32,554
Is there…

176
00:16:34,306 --> 00:16:37,768
anyone you're in conflict with?

177
00:16:41,146 --> 00:16:43,482
Some may not like me.

178
00:16:44,733 --> 00:16:45,984
But that doesn't mean

179
00:16:47,152 --> 00:16:50,239
I should stop myself
from doing what I must do.

180
00:16:53,617 --> 00:16:55,327
With all due respect,

181
00:16:56,578 --> 00:17:00,958
why don't you re-examine
your relations with those around you?

182
00:17:01,875 --> 00:17:05,420
If you're in conflict with anyone,

183
00:17:05,504 --> 00:17:09,758
you might want to work things out
with them smoothly.

184
00:17:13,512 --> 00:17:14,847
Afterward…

185
00:17:16,640 --> 00:17:18,725
It must've been three months or so.

186
00:17:19,601 --> 00:17:21,728
I got a call from Mr. Yoon.

187
00:17:28,735 --> 00:17:29,736
Hello?

188
00:17:30,237 --> 00:17:33,031
Prosecutor Shin, I figured it out.

189
00:17:34,449 --> 00:17:39,371
He probably visited those
who may have suffered because of him.

190
00:17:46,837 --> 00:17:50,674
His first destination was
the bully student's house.

191
00:18:09,818 --> 00:18:14,156
There, he unexpectedly saw
the student's father

192
00:18:14,740 --> 00:18:17,784
with a prosecutor he'd seen
at the Prosecutors' Office.

193
00:18:20,120 --> 00:18:22,080
A prosecutor?

194
00:18:22,164 --> 00:18:26,293
He'd only seen him a few times
as he frequented the Prosecutors' Office.

195
00:18:26,376 --> 00:18:28,712
He didn't know his name or department.

196
00:18:30,339 --> 00:18:32,674
He meant to ask me about him,

197
00:18:32,758 --> 00:18:34,635
but then, he thought it'd get complicated

198
00:18:35,594 --> 00:18:37,596
if everything turned out
to be a misunderstanding.

199
00:18:38,722 --> 00:18:43,310
So, he sought another way
to look into it carefully.

200
00:18:49,650 --> 00:18:50,859
Hello?

201
00:18:50,943 --> 00:18:54,321
Prosecutor Shin, I figured it out.

202
00:18:54,988 --> 00:18:56,615
What do you mean by that?

203
00:18:56,698 --> 00:18:58,992
I recorded their conversation.

204
00:18:59,952 --> 00:19:03,455
I hid the recorder just in case.

205
00:19:04,456 --> 00:19:06,875
You're the only one I can trust.

206
00:19:07,542 --> 00:19:08,543
Please,

207
00:19:09,419 --> 00:19:11,463
make sure to reveal the truth.

208
00:19:13,632 --> 00:19:15,008
Just a moment, Mr. Yoon.

209
00:19:22,474 --> 00:19:23,475
Yes.

210
00:19:28,855 --> 00:19:29,856
Got it.

211
00:19:30,691 --> 00:19:32,025
I'm on my way now.

212
00:19:32,859 --> 00:19:33,902
And…

213
00:19:36,321 --> 00:19:39,366
my memory ends

214
00:19:40,450 --> 00:19:42,244
when I went to collect the recorder.

215
00:19:46,665 --> 00:19:47,666
That day,

216
00:19:49,584 --> 00:19:50,877
Mr. Yoon

217
00:19:51,962 --> 00:19:53,797
was found to have committed suicide.

218
00:19:54,423 --> 00:19:55,424
What?

219
00:19:57,092 --> 00:19:58,302
That's absurd.

220
00:19:59,970 --> 00:20:02,222
The last time we spoke,

221
00:20:04,057 --> 00:20:08,020
he was full of hope
that he'd be cleared of false charges.

222
00:20:09,479 --> 00:20:10,480
But he killed himself?

223
00:20:20,198 --> 00:20:21,199
Did I…

224
00:20:22,617 --> 00:20:26,288
die on the same day as Mr. Yoon?

225
00:20:30,083 --> 00:20:31,084
Yes.

226
00:20:33,128 --> 00:20:36,715
And your body tested positive
for narcotics.

227
00:20:38,300 --> 00:20:41,470
Your cabinet was
filled with evidence of corruption.

228
00:20:42,054 --> 00:20:43,055
Narcotics

229
00:20:44,806 --> 00:20:46,641
and evidence of corruption?

230
00:20:48,060 --> 00:20:50,103
I don't get it.

231
00:20:50,187 --> 00:20:51,313
People thought

232
00:20:52,522 --> 00:20:56,777
you took bribes from someone
and used your position as a prosecutor

233
00:20:57,402 --> 00:20:59,696
to torment Mr. Yoon relentlessly,

234
00:21:00,614 --> 00:21:01,740
which caused

235
00:21:02,657 --> 00:21:04,868
Mr. Yoon to commit suicide.

236
00:21:04,951 --> 00:21:07,371
What are you talking about?
That's ridiculous!

237
00:21:13,210 --> 00:21:15,212
It's not true.

238
00:21:15,837 --> 00:21:18,924
I-rang, none of that makes sense.

239
00:21:19,007 --> 00:21:20,300
I'm sorry, Dad.

240
00:21:21,676 --> 00:21:23,261
I thought the same

241
00:21:24,304 --> 00:21:25,764
as everyone else.

242
00:21:27,474 --> 00:21:30,852
I wanted to believe otherwise,

243
00:21:32,646 --> 00:21:34,981
but I blamed and resented
a corrupt prosecutor

244
00:21:36,817 --> 00:21:38,443
whom the world pointed fingers at.

245
00:21:39,986 --> 00:21:42,697
That's why I was so harsh on you

246
00:21:42,781 --> 00:21:44,574
when you showed up.

247
00:21:46,868 --> 00:21:47,869
I see.

248
00:21:54,751 --> 00:21:55,919
But in the end,

249
00:21:57,337 --> 00:21:58,880
you decided to believe me.

250
00:22:01,133 --> 00:22:03,093
The one person who believes in me.

251
00:22:06,304 --> 00:22:07,305
Yes, that.

252
00:22:08,306 --> 00:22:10,100
That's all I need.

253
00:22:14,229 --> 00:22:15,647
What I remembered of you…

254
00:22:17,691 --> 00:22:19,151
was right.

255
00:22:26,825 --> 00:22:27,868
From now on,

256
00:22:28,618 --> 00:22:29,703
we'll set things right.

257
00:22:32,330 --> 00:22:33,540
I'll do it for you.

258
00:22:36,209 --> 00:22:37,460
Thank you.

259
00:23:08,825 --> 00:23:10,452
I have something to tell you, Father.

260
00:23:12,162 --> 00:23:13,205
Take a seat there.

261
00:23:25,133 --> 00:23:27,677
I met the shaman just now.

262
00:23:30,138 --> 00:23:31,514
Shin I-rang's father.

263
00:23:32,682 --> 00:23:36,561
Why do you bother with him?
Shin Gi-jung died 20 years ago.

264
00:23:39,981 --> 00:23:42,359
Let's say Shin I-rang
does see his father's spirit.

265
00:23:42,442 --> 00:23:44,027
But what does it have to do with you?

266
00:23:44,819 --> 00:23:46,613
Why do you care so much that you even

267
00:23:47,322 --> 00:23:48,949
locked up the shaman in this building?

268
00:23:49,491 --> 00:23:52,744
I didn't expect you'd discover all that.

269
00:23:53,245 --> 00:23:54,246
Good job.

270
00:23:55,038 --> 00:23:56,331
Father.

271
00:23:59,334 --> 00:24:02,254
Shin Gi-jung was my direct junior.

272
00:24:04,506 --> 00:24:07,842
He was a great prosecutor
of unmatched diligence

273
00:24:07,926 --> 00:24:10,762
and had profound insight in every case.

274
00:24:16,184 --> 00:24:17,185
Hello?

275
00:24:17,269 --> 00:24:18,436
Byung-il.

276
00:24:18,520 --> 00:24:19,813
My hunch was right.

277
00:24:21,773 --> 00:24:24,150
What's the occasion?
It's not like you to get so worked up.

278
00:24:24,234 --> 00:24:28,113
I told you some forces were
intentionally harassing Mr. Yoon.

279
00:24:30,156 --> 00:24:31,283
It was a senior prosecutor.

280
00:24:33,618 --> 00:24:34,828
What are you talking about?

281
00:24:34,911 --> 00:24:38,039
A prosecutor took bribes
from the bully student's father

282
00:24:38,123 --> 00:24:39,958
and targeted Mr. Yoon for investigation.

283
00:24:41,209 --> 00:24:43,086
What… Are you sure about this?

284
00:24:43,878 --> 00:24:45,839
Act rashly

285
00:24:45,922 --> 00:24:48,633
and you might get the blunt end
of being labeled as a whistleblower.

286
00:24:48,717 --> 00:24:51,052
So I'm going to double-check it.

287
00:24:51,886 --> 00:24:54,848
Mr. Yoon told me
where he hid the recorded evidence.

288
00:24:55,515 --> 00:24:57,767
I'm on my way to collect it.

289
00:24:58,351 --> 00:24:59,436
Gi-jung.

290
00:25:00,020 --> 00:25:01,521
Be careful.

291
00:25:01,604 --> 00:25:02,605
Of course, I will.

292
00:25:02,689 --> 00:25:05,650
Don't worry.
I'll talk to you again when I'm back.

293
00:25:06,651 --> 00:25:09,612
But I didn't hear from him after that.

294
00:25:11,406 --> 00:25:15,201
Later that night, I was informed
Gi-jung and Mr. Yoon were found dead.

295
00:25:16,619 --> 00:25:17,620
So what?

296
00:25:17,704 --> 00:25:18,830
Shin Gi-jung is

297
00:25:20,165 --> 00:25:22,792
the only person who knows
where the recorder is.

298
00:25:22,876 --> 00:25:25,045
Why are you so concerned
with this recorder?

299
00:25:29,758 --> 00:25:33,428
I'm the chief prosecutor
who harassed Yoon Dae-myeong

300
00:25:34,512 --> 00:25:36,097
at the bully student's father's request.

301
00:25:37,640 --> 00:25:38,641
What?

302
00:25:49,486 --> 00:25:50,487
Why, Father?

303
00:25:50,570 --> 00:25:51,863
I did it to survive.

304
00:25:55,575 --> 00:25:58,244
At the time, I was losing my footing

305
00:25:58,328 --> 00:26:01,081
after the chief prosecutor I served
was sidelined.

306
00:26:02,582 --> 00:26:05,877
That was when I got an offer.

307
00:26:05,960 --> 00:26:09,714
DAEHUN LAW FIRM

308
00:26:09,798 --> 00:26:12,592
I heard you're looking
for a law firm to join.

309
00:26:15,053 --> 00:26:18,306
If you quietly take care
of my daughter's case,

310
00:26:19,140 --> 00:26:21,935
I'll bring you on board
with preferential treatment.

311
00:26:25,188 --> 00:26:26,481
Well,

312
00:26:27,857 --> 00:26:30,193
I can do that much myself.

313
00:26:31,194 --> 00:26:32,570
I'm not sure

314
00:26:33,738 --> 00:26:37,033
if it's worth taking such a risk.

315
00:26:39,160 --> 00:26:41,246
Then what do you want in exchange?

316
00:26:44,541 --> 00:26:45,542
A future.

317
00:26:48,211 --> 00:26:49,754
A guaranteed future

318
00:26:51,047 --> 00:26:52,382
that can never be shaken.

319
00:26:56,553 --> 00:27:00,640
PERSONAL BACKGROUND INFORMATION
NAME: YOON DAE-MYEONG

320
00:27:09,190 --> 00:27:11,734
It was the first and last time
I ever abandoned my convictions

321
00:27:11,818 --> 00:27:13,069
as a man of the law.

322
00:27:14,320 --> 00:27:17,615
I hired people
to file complaints and lawsuits.

323
00:27:18,616 --> 00:27:21,286
Yoon Dae-myeong gave up on his life
too easily.

324
00:27:23,246 --> 00:27:24,247
And then,

325
00:27:25,957 --> 00:27:27,750
I became the owner of Taebaek.

326
00:27:30,336 --> 00:27:31,337
Did you

327
00:27:32,881 --> 00:27:34,549
kill Yoon Dae-myeong

328
00:27:35,550 --> 00:27:36,718
and Shin Gi-jung?

329
00:27:39,637 --> 00:27:40,638
No.

330
00:27:41,514 --> 00:27:43,224
I didn't kill anyone.

331
00:27:53,026 --> 00:27:57,864
CHARCOAL BRIQUETTE

332
00:28:14,214 --> 00:28:17,592
Like I said, he was so hopeless
that he took his own life.

333
00:28:31,356 --> 00:28:34,776
And Shin Gi-jung died
in an unfortunate accident.

334
00:28:43,618 --> 00:28:44,619
Yeah?

335
00:28:45,161 --> 00:28:46,412
It's all been taken care of.

336
00:29:42,635 --> 00:29:43,887
I had no idea

337
00:29:45,138 --> 00:29:47,307
Gi-jung was using drugs.

338
00:30:15,209 --> 00:30:20,340
Additionally, all of his other
corrupt acts were found in his cabinet.

339
00:30:22,175 --> 00:30:23,384
That's what happened.

340
00:30:25,511 --> 00:30:27,805
Shin Gi-jung committed the corruption,

341
00:30:29,515 --> 00:30:31,935
but I can't say I'm fully innocent.

342
00:30:38,858 --> 00:30:39,984
Are you disappointed in me?

343
00:30:43,446 --> 00:30:44,447
No.

344
00:30:46,282 --> 00:30:49,786
I finally feel a connection to you.

345
00:30:51,955 --> 00:30:52,956
You trusted me

346
00:30:54,207 --> 00:30:56,292
and told me everything honestly.

347
00:31:04,008 --> 00:31:06,135
If Shin Gi-jung's spirit is back,

348
00:31:06,219 --> 00:31:09,055
he'll try to find the recorder for sure.

349
00:31:10,056 --> 00:31:12,058
He'll try to suffocate me with it.

350
00:31:13,184 --> 00:31:15,061
If no one stops him,

351
00:31:15,144 --> 00:31:16,938
Taebaek will go down.

352
00:31:17,021 --> 00:31:18,064
No.

353
00:31:19,232 --> 00:31:21,609
Taebaek will never go down, Father.

354
00:31:23,361 --> 00:31:24,862
Don't worry.

355
00:31:24,946 --> 00:31:25,947
I'll stop him.

356
00:31:26,030 --> 00:31:28,282
There are people better suited
for this kind of work.

357
00:31:50,513 --> 00:31:51,973
Don't make any rash moves.

358
00:31:53,558 --> 00:31:55,893
Wait for the perfect moment.

359
00:32:09,949 --> 00:32:11,159
Yes, Father.

360
00:32:17,290 --> 00:32:20,001
Is there anyone else
who knows about the recorder

361
00:32:20,668 --> 00:32:22,420
other than Mr. Yoon?

362
00:32:23,004 --> 00:32:24,297
Yes.

363
00:32:24,380 --> 00:32:25,506
Who?

364
00:32:27,467 --> 00:32:29,677
Chief Prosecutor Yang Byung-il.
He was my senior.

365
00:32:34,891 --> 00:32:35,975
I know him.

366
00:32:36,934 --> 00:32:41,230
He's the chairman
of a big law firm named Taebaek.

367
00:32:42,315 --> 00:32:43,691
It can't be him.

368
00:32:43,775 --> 00:32:46,027
We were like brothers.

369
00:32:46,652 --> 00:32:47,820
The culprit

370
00:32:49,322 --> 00:32:53,576
tried to stop the evidence from going out
even by killing you and Mr. Yoon.

371
00:32:54,535 --> 00:32:58,081
You know where the recorder is, right?

372
00:33:03,503 --> 00:33:04,921
The Yoon Dae-myeong case?

373
00:33:07,048 --> 00:33:10,051
I checked the records Mr. Yoon collected

374
00:33:10,134 --> 00:33:12,470
and noticed a lot of issues
in the initial investigation.

375
00:33:12,553 --> 00:33:15,890
Na-hyun, it was closed
as suicide 20 years ago.

376
00:33:15,973 --> 00:33:17,225
It may not be just one.

377
00:33:17,850 --> 00:33:19,769
-What?
-The victim, I mean.

378
00:33:20,853 --> 00:33:22,939
If Mr. Yoon was murdered,

379
00:33:23,022 --> 00:33:27,193
the death of Shin Gi-jung, who died
on the same day, is suspicious as well.

380
00:33:27,819 --> 00:33:29,487
There may be a connection.

381
00:33:31,864 --> 00:33:33,908
So, how do you want me to help?

382
00:33:34,492 --> 00:33:37,370
I want to meet the first witness.

383
00:33:38,037 --> 00:33:41,415
There are parts
where the statement doesn't add up.

384
00:33:41,916 --> 00:33:46,045
The witness said
he discovered the scene at 10 p.m.

385
00:33:46,129 --> 00:33:50,091
But the record says
the report was made at 3 a.m.

386
00:33:50,675 --> 00:33:53,302
He also said
the police were already there,

387
00:33:53,386 --> 00:33:55,680
but there's no dispatch record
at the local police station.

388
00:33:56,264 --> 00:33:57,765
It happened a long time ago.

389
00:33:57,849 --> 00:33:59,767
The witness may not still be in Korea

390
00:33:59,851 --> 00:34:01,435
or may no longer be alive.

391
00:34:01,519 --> 00:34:03,271
Still, look into it for me.

392
00:34:05,606 --> 00:34:06,858
I won't give you personal details.

393
00:34:07,567 --> 00:34:10,486
I'll contact him and ask
if he's okay to meet you.

394
00:34:11,195 --> 00:34:12,488
Thanks.

395
00:34:25,793 --> 00:34:26,919
Looking for something?

396
00:34:29,130 --> 00:34:30,131
Mom.

397
00:34:31,591 --> 00:34:32,842
Where is

398
00:34:33,718 --> 00:34:37,805
the brown handbag Dad bought you
when you were newlyweds?

399
00:34:39,056 --> 00:34:40,516
Why do you need it all of a sudden?

400
00:34:42,226 --> 00:34:44,228
-The thing is--
-Did…

401
00:34:46,564 --> 00:34:49,025
your dad say he put something in it?

402
00:35:25,895 --> 00:35:26,896
But Mom…

403
00:35:27,813 --> 00:35:29,482
how did you know?

404
00:35:37,740 --> 00:35:39,325
A few days ago,

405
00:35:40,159 --> 00:35:44,747
I found a paper crane
in the lunch box I packed for you.

406
00:35:48,251 --> 00:35:51,128
The same paper crane your dad used to put

407
00:35:51,879 --> 00:35:53,506
in his lunch box.

408
00:36:08,396 --> 00:36:09,397
Then,

409
00:36:10,314 --> 00:36:11,774
why did you act like

410
00:36:12,775 --> 00:36:14,110
you didn't know?

411
00:36:19,031 --> 00:36:20,283
The truth is…

412
00:36:22,285 --> 00:36:25,204
when I heard you could see ghosts,

413
00:36:26,330 --> 00:36:28,916
I hoped your dad would come.

414
00:36:30,501 --> 00:36:33,462
As I saw you right wrongs for the ghosts,

415
00:36:34,088 --> 00:36:36,716
my wish grew bigger.

416
00:36:37,258 --> 00:36:38,259
But…

417
00:36:39,802 --> 00:36:42,638
I knew how painful and hard it'd be

418
00:36:42,722 --> 00:36:45,975
for you to meet your dad again,

419
00:36:47,393 --> 00:36:49,186
so I couldn't bring myself to tell you.

420
00:36:51,355 --> 00:36:52,356
Mom.

421
00:36:53,482 --> 00:36:54,483
It turned out

422
00:36:56,110 --> 00:36:57,862
Dad was framed.

423
00:37:05,578 --> 00:37:07,538
Where is he?

424
00:37:07,621 --> 00:37:08,748
At the office.

425
00:37:10,416 --> 00:37:12,001
When everything is over,

426
00:37:13,252 --> 00:37:16,756
he wants to meet the family
with his head held high.

427
00:37:19,800 --> 00:37:24,347
He's a ghost now,
but he's still so inflexible.

428
00:37:25,973 --> 00:37:30,019
Okay. Bring him home
after everything is taken care of.

429
00:37:30,686 --> 00:37:32,688
And tell him

430
00:37:32,772 --> 00:37:34,315
that I, Park Gyeong-hwa,

431
00:37:35,066 --> 00:37:39,070
believe what Shin Gi-jung says
even if the world comes to an end.

432
00:37:42,490 --> 00:37:43,532
Okay.

433
00:38:37,795 --> 00:38:38,838
This is Yang Do-kyung.

434
00:38:38,921 --> 00:38:40,214
Oh.

435
00:38:40,297 --> 00:38:42,591
I heard from the Chairman.

436
00:38:42,675 --> 00:38:44,593
I was waiting for your call

437
00:38:45,386 --> 00:38:47,054
to tell you something.

438
00:38:48,097 --> 00:38:49,098
I'm listening.

439
00:38:49,682 --> 00:38:54,145
One of my boys got a call
from a prosecutor just a while ago.

440
00:38:55,146 --> 00:38:59,942
He said an attorney wanted to inquire
about the Yoon case from 20 years ago.

441
00:39:00,025 --> 00:39:01,026
Who's that?

442
00:39:01,110 --> 00:39:04,363
I looked into this attorney he mentioned.

443
00:39:06,991 --> 00:39:08,033
Her name is Han Na-hyun.

444
00:39:08,993 --> 00:39:11,495
She's a colleague of Shin I-rang.

445
00:39:12,121 --> 00:39:13,747
If the Chairman hears this--

446
00:39:13,831 --> 00:39:15,291
Don't mind her.

447
00:39:16,083 --> 00:39:17,084
Why's that?

448
00:39:17,168 --> 00:39:18,794
Attorney Han is one of us.

449
00:39:19,462 --> 00:39:20,463
Leave her be.

450
00:39:49,867 --> 00:39:52,828
This is where you wanted to come with me?

451
00:39:53,579 --> 00:39:54,580
Yeah.

452
00:39:55,664 --> 00:39:56,832
I wanted to come.

453
00:39:58,751 --> 00:39:59,960
This place hasn't changed.

454
00:40:01,837 --> 00:40:05,257
I always dropped by
whenever I faced big cases.

455
00:40:07,885 --> 00:40:09,595
All dressed up like that?

456
00:40:13,140 --> 00:40:15,976
I've worn the suit for 22 years
and I can't take it off.

457
00:40:30,241 --> 00:40:32,826
I came here with you sometimes
when you were little, remember?

458
00:40:34,119 --> 00:40:35,120
I do.

459
00:40:37,540 --> 00:40:39,041
I should be peeling it for you.

460
00:40:40,292 --> 00:40:41,877
But I can't even hold it.

461
00:40:44,672 --> 00:40:47,675
I can do it on my own now.

462
00:40:51,887 --> 00:40:53,097
Dad.

463
00:41:04,149 --> 00:41:05,150
Dad!

464
00:41:05,776 --> 00:41:07,361
You have to give me a warning.

465
00:41:08,153 --> 00:41:10,614
You used to like it when I peeled it

466
00:41:10,698 --> 00:41:13,701
and dipped it in salt for you like this.

467
00:41:22,042 --> 00:41:23,043
It's good.

468
00:41:26,964 --> 00:41:29,341
Boiled eggs are good
at the bathhouse indeed.

469
00:41:29,883 --> 00:41:31,218
They are.

470
00:41:31,302 --> 00:41:32,595
Hard to swallow, right?

471
00:41:34,513 --> 00:41:37,516
SUJEONG BATHHOUSE

472
00:41:46,609 --> 00:41:47,610
Shall we go?

473
00:41:51,780 --> 00:41:54,283
PITTER-PATTER BUTCHER-STYLE BBQ

474
00:42:12,176 --> 00:42:13,177
Mr. Yang.

475
00:42:14,678 --> 00:42:15,929
What brings you here?

476
00:42:16,013 --> 00:42:17,890
Stop what you're doing now.

477
00:42:19,058 --> 00:42:20,059
Why?

478
00:42:20,142 --> 00:42:21,560
You don't have to return to Taebaek.

479
00:42:22,186 --> 00:42:24,438
You can work with Shin I-rang.

480
00:42:25,064 --> 00:42:27,316
But don't try to discover the truth
behind this case.

481
00:42:27,399 --> 00:42:29,902
-Why shouldn't I discover the truth?
-It's dangerous.

482
00:42:32,488 --> 00:42:34,448
You know what I'm up to

483
00:42:34,948 --> 00:42:36,492
and that it's dangerous.

484
00:42:37,701 --> 00:42:39,578
Then, you must know
who'll put me in danger.

485
00:42:42,122 --> 00:42:43,624
Who is it?

486
00:42:49,755 --> 00:42:51,423
I'm telling you
because I care about you

487
00:42:52,883 --> 00:42:54,385
and we were colleagues once.

488
00:42:56,887 --> 00:42:58,347
I warned you.

489
00:43:16,198 --> 00:43:17,241
Prosecutor Kim?

490
00:43:17,324 --> 00:43:18,409
Hi, Na-hyun.

491
00:43:18,492 --> 00:43:21,578
I went over the Yoon Dae-myeong case
after you left.

492
00:43:21,662 --> 00:43:24,832
The first witness was
a member of the Four Dragons Gang

493
00:43:24,915 --> 00:43:27,543
which was dismantled
in Chinatown 20 years ago.

494
00:43:28,127 --> 00:43:29,503
A Four Dragons member?

495
00:43:29,586 --> 00:43:31,463
What's more important is

496
00:43:32,506 --> 00:43:34,717
that the prosecutor
who dismantled the gang

497
00:43:36,552 --> 00:43:37,886
was Shin Gi-jung.

498
00:43:57,990 --> 00:43:59,783
OCTOBER 10, 2003
SEOMGANG ELECTRONICS

499
00:44:01,160 --> 00:44:04,496
SEOMGANG ELECTRONICS

500
00:44:15,966 --> 00:44:19,470
I'm the son of Prosecutor Shin Gi-jung
from the Incheon Prosecutors' Office.

501
00:45:23,617 --> 00:45:26,828
SHIN I-RANG LAW OFFICE
PITTER-PATTER BUTCHER-STYLE BBQ

502
00:45:28,914 --> 00:45:29,915
Attorney Shin?

503
00:45:40,842 --> 00:45:42,302
It's not him.

504
00:46:09,663 --> 00:46:10,664
Who are you?

505
00:46:13,875 --> 00:46:15,460
Why aren't you saying anything?

506
00:46:20,507 --> 00:46:22,718
I can't be sure

507
00:46:23,594 --> 00:46:26,013
if you're allies

508
00:46:26,972 --> 00:46:28,181
or enemies

509
00:46:29,808 --> 00:46:30,809
with my I-rang.

510
00:46:32,311 --> 00:46:33,687
Enemies?

511
00:46:34,271 --> 00:46:36,064
You don't know how much I like…

512
00:46:38,483 --> 00:46:39,818
I mean, help him.

513
00:46:43,447 --> 00:46:45,240
Oh, check the necklace.

514
00:46:45,949 --> 00:46:48,368
My number's engraved on it.

515
00:46:57,377 --> 00:46:59,129
SHIN I-RANG
010-0976-1425

516
00:47:03,425 --> 00:47:04,593
ATTORNEY SHIN I-RANG

517
00:47:06,011 --> 00:47:07,971
ATTORNEY HAN NA-HYUN
010-0976-1425

518
00:47:08,055 --> 00:47:09,222
See?

519
00:47:15,896 --> 00:47:17,648
So, who are you?

520
00:47:17,731 --> 00:47:22,069
Why do you call Attorney Shin "my I-rang"?

521
00:47:23,445 --> 00:47:24,696
Are you a friend of his?

522
00:47:24,780 --> 00:47:27,240
Or… a family member?

523
00:47:29,284 --> 00:47:31,453
-Yes.
-What?

524
00:47:32,204 --> 00:47:33,455
Nice to meet you.

525
00:47:34,539 --> 00:47:36,083
I know it may be confusing,

526
00:47:37,209 --> 00:47:39,836
but I'm I-rang's dad…

527
00:47:41,922 --> 00:47:43,340
Shin Gi-jung.

528
00:47:44,591 --> 00:47:46,635
Forgive me for being rude--

529
00:47:46,718 --> 00:47:48,387
No, that's okay.

530
00:47:48,470 --> 00:47:49,888
Um…

531
00:47:49,971 --> 00:47:50,972
Father.

532
00:47:51,932 --> 00:47:54,851
Excuse me for being disrespectful.

533
00:47:55,727 --> 00:47:56,937
I'm so sorry.

534
00:47:57,020 --> 00:47:58,855
No, please don't be.

535
00:47:58,939 --> 00:48:00,190
I'm rather glad

536
00:48:00,774 --> 00:48:03,819
to see how much you care about my son.

537
00:48:05,487 --> 00:48:06,738
It was nice.

538
00:48:07,948 --> 00:48:09,866
Let me officially introduce myself.

539
00:48:11,702 --> 00:48:14,830
I'm colleagues with Attorney Shin I-rang.

540
00:48:15,414 --> 00:48:16,998
I'm Attorney Han Na-hyun.

541
00:48:17,082 --> 00:48:18,375
Nice to meet you.

542
00:48:21,586 --> 00:48:25,215
So, why aren't you waking him up?

543
00:48:28,260 --> 00:48:30,971
If you don't know how, let me--

544
00:48:31,054 --> 00:48:32,264
No, that's not it.

545
00:48:33,432 --> 00:48:34,433
I just…

546
00:48:38,520 --> 00:48:43,233
This recorder has a conversation
between those who framed Mr. Yoon.

547
00:48:45,152 --> 00:48:50,031
If it holds any kind of truth
that may put I-rang in danger…

548
00:48:52,868 --> 00:48:54,703
I'd like for him to be unaware of it.

549
00:48:56,037 --> 00:48:57,914
I cannot put my son in danger

550
00:48:57,998 --> 00:49:00,500
trying to resolve my own resentment.

551
00:49:04,129 --> 00:49:06,381
Attorney Shin remembered you

552
00:49:07,674 --> 00:49:10,051
as a righteous hero.

553
00:49:11,678 --> 00:49:14,973
Although you passed away
under false accusations,

554
00:49:15,557 --> 00:49:17,559
he wanted to believe in you to the end.

555
00:49:19,644 --> 00:49:21,897
That led him to become an attorney.

556
00:49:24,191 --> 00:49:29,279
Your son is more diligent
and responsible than anyone.

557
00:49:31,281 --> 00:49:34,201
He's handled a lot of difficult cases

558
00:49:35,076 --> 00:49:36,453
on his own.

559
00:49:38,205 --> 00:49:41,124
I'm sure he will do the same this time.

560
00:49:42,918 --> 00:49:44,002
Attorney Han.

561
00:49:47,130 --> 00:49:49,883
Thank you for letting me realize…

562
00:49:53,804 --> 00:49:54,805
that I should…

563
00:49:57,641 --> 00:49:59,935
leave the decision to him.

564
00:50:04,773 --> 00:50:06,858
Could you wake him up?

565
00:50:07,692 --> 00:50:08,819
Sure.

566
00:50:31,258 --> 00:50:32,634
Attorney Han?

567
00:50:33,969 --> 00:50:35,011
Are you okay?

568
00:50:37,681 --> 00:50:38,682
Why are we…

569
00:50:40,809 --> 00:50:41,935
I met your father.

570
00:50:43,562 --> 00:50:44,563
And…

571
00:50:45,856 --> 00:50:47,649
I know what that recorder is.

572
00:50:49,693 --> 00:50:52,237
I'm sorry for keeping it from you.

573
00:50:52,320 --> 00:50:55,448
It's all right.
I've been through it, you know.

574
00:50:57,909 --> 00:51:00,078
You were right.

575
00:51:02,080 --> 00:51:03,456
I was

576
00:51:04,457 --> 00:51:06,459
greatly mistaken about my dad.

577
00:51:08,670 --> 00:51:10,046
It's such a relief.

578
00:51:15,302 --> 00:51:17,846
You should check the recording now.

579
00:51:18,430 --> 00:51:19,931
Listen to it with me.

580
00:51:20,015 --> 00:51:21,474
Let's go inside.

581
00:51:22,267 --> 00:51:23,560
Okay.

582
00:51:27,772 --> 00:51:28,773
Hello?

583
00:51:30,859 --> 00:51:33,111
Shin I-rang arrived
at the office just now.

584
00:51:33,194 --> 00:51:34,946
PITTER-PATTER BUTCHER-STYLE BBQ

585
00:51:35,030 --> 00:51:36,656
Get the recorder from him first.

586
00:51:36,740 --> 00:51:38,617
Sure, but…

587
00:51:39,200 --> 00:51:42,704
Attorney Han Na-hyun is with him.

588
00:51:44,080 --> 00:51:46,249
What do we do about her?

589
00:51:51,171 --> 00:51:52,339
Do-kyung.

590
00:52:07,520 --> 00:52:08,647
Who are you people?

591
00:52:15,612 --> 00:52:16,738
Wow.

592
00:52:16,821 --> 00:52:19,449
I love the vibe of this office.

593
00:52:21,826 --> 00:52:23,703
It's perfect for a funeral.

594
00:52:27,832 --> 00:52:30,001
Oh, that must be it.

595
00:52:30,543 --> 00:52:32,921
-Bring it over.
-Says who?

596
00:52:36,216 --> 00:52:37,342
I-rang.

597
00:52:40,053 --> 00:52:41,972
Trust me and grab that thing.

598
00:52:54,734 --> 00:52:55,735
Fine.

599
00:52:57,570 --> 00:52:59,739
Here, take it.

600
00:53:25,265 --> 00:53:27,684
You still haven't turned over a new leaf,
Lee Tae-geon?

601
00:53:28,935 --> 00:53:29,936
What?

602
00:53:30,520 --> 00:53:32,480
-Boss!
-Are you okay, sir?

603
00:53:32,564 --> 00:53:34,482
What are you waiting for? Get him!

604
00:54:04,471 --> 00:54:05,889
Go get her, boys.

605
00:54:20,070 --> 00:54:21,071
Head!

606
00:55:09,786 --> 00:55:10,954
Shin I-rang!

607
00:55:18,378 --> 00:55:20,505
I don't care if you're ghost or human.

608
00:55:23,508 --> 00:55:24,634
The recorder.

609
00:55:27,512 --> 00:55:28,638
Bring it here.

610
00:55:35,061 --> 00:55:36,396
Wait.

611
00:55:38,356 --> 00:55:39,357
I get it,

612
00:55:40,191 --> 00:55:41,192
so stop.

613
00:55:46,114 --> 00:55:48,575
No, I-rang. Don't do it.

614
00:55:49,993 --> 00:55:51,661
I can't let you go like this.

615
00:55:52,912 --> 00:55:53,913
I'm sorry.

616
00:56:30,241 --> 00:56:31,618
Drag him here.

617
00:56:41,794 --> 00:56:44,464
You'll never get to listen to this.

618
00:56:45,256 --> 00:56:46,257
Got it?

619
00:56:54,265 --> 00:56:55,391
Shin I-rang!

620
00:57:08,905 --> 00:57:10,615
I'll never lose it again.

621
00:57:52,740 --> 00:57:56,661
SPECIAL THANKS TO
CHOI WON-YOUNG AND JUNG JAE-SUNG

622
00:58:12,760 --> 00:58:16,681
SHIN I-RANG
010-0976-1425

623
00:58:23,646 --> 00:58:24,731
Welcome.

624
00:58:25,565 --> 00:58:26,649
It…

625
00:58:26,733 --> 00:58:28,401
It must've been a long way… Oof!

626
00:58:28,484 --> 00:58:29,944
-I'll go again.
-Okay, cut.

627
00:58:30,945 --> 00:58:31,946
Mister.

628
00:58:33,031 --> 00:58:35,742
I want to go there.

629
00:58:36,951 --> 00:58:38,119
Are you…

630
00:58:39,078 --> 00:58:40,204
Hello?

631
00:58:41,789 --> 00:58:42,790
Let's go again.

632
00:58:44,500 --> 00:58:47,086
You're going back in there?

633
00:58:47,170 --> 00:58:48,630
They thought I was a woman--

634
00:58:49,172 --> 00:58:51,132
They thought I was a gangster
and cornered me.

635
00:58:51,215 --> 00:58:52,383
Sorry!

636
00:58:52,467 --> 00:58:53,468
My bad.

637
00:58:54,135 --> 00:58:57,430
The shine of his cheap shoes shows

638
00:58:57,513 --> 00:58:58,890
his diligent nature.

639
00:58:59,432 --> 00:59:02,143
The leather surface appears
to be in good condition,

640
00:59:02,226 --> 00:59:04,062
which shows…

641
00:59:05,647 --> 00:59:06,648
I'm sorry.

642
00:59:07,190 --> 00:59:08,441
Tae-in, you do it.

643
00:59:08,524 --> 00:59:10,360
Do we have a large party?

644
00:59:10,443 --> 00:59:11,819
I-rang is strange.

645
00:59:13,154 --> 00:59:14,739
Oh, sorry. That's not the line.

646
00:59:22,038 --> 00:59:23,039
Ow, that hurts.

647
00:59:24,457 --> 00:59:25,667
It didn't break.

648
00:59:25,750 --> 00:59:29,671
Subtitle translation by: Eunjin Erica Kim
